# Changelog — nats-server-auth-authz-hardening

## v1.0.0 — 2026-06-19

**What changed:** Initial creation.

**Why:** Captured a PLANNING learning (verification: `unverified`) from an Odysseus
session on how to plan NATS server-side auth/authz hardening for the
HomericIntelligence mesh on top of the existing ADR-008 TLS PKI. The durable,
generalizable lesson is to reuse the existing X.509 mutual-cert trust chain via
`verify_and_map` (client) + `verify` (cluster/leafnode) and subject-scoped
`accounts{}` mapped to the ADR-005 `hi.*` schema, rather than standing up
decentralized operator/NKey/JWT (which needs an operator keypair, JWT resolver,
and out-of-band issuance pipeline that do not exist on disk). AID v0.2.0 Ed25519
+ scoped JWT recorded as the documented FUTURE path.

Key recorded findings: TLS already landed via ADR-008 (PRs #290/#292) on every
listener; issue #175's cited line numbers (server.conf:12-21 "no tls block")
were STALE; no `verify`/`accounts{}` present yet; ADRs are append-only (next was
009, never edit ADR-008). The plan was NOT executed and no `nats-server -t`
parse check was run, so the cert→user mapping semantics, JetStream API subject
scoping, `accounts{}` syntax, and `accounts{}`-in-leaf.conf validity remain
unverified risks.
